Name: dengue shock syndrome
Definition: A dengue disease that involves the most severe form of dengue fever

Name: obsolete Tahyna virus encephalitis
Definition: A California virus encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain

Name: asymptomatic dengue
Definition: A dengue disease that results_in infection

Name: dengue hemorrhagic fever
Definition: A dengue disease that occurs when a person experiences a second infection with a heterologous Dengue virus serotype

Name: obsolete infiltrative lung tuberculosis
Definition: A pulmonary tuberculosis that is characterized by filling of airspaces with fluid

Name: obsolete Wuchereria bancrofti filariasis
Definition: A filarial elephantiasis that involves parasitic infection of the lymphatic system by a filarial worm Wuchereria bancrofti
